title: ‘For good government, you need good Opposition’: Taylor’s new leadership is a ‘great thing'
description: Labor MP Ash Ambihaipahar described what it was like seeing the Opposition go through a leadership spill.  “This is a great thing, but also I think it’s a sad thing for the Australian community,” Ms Ambihaipahar told Sky News Australia.   “For good government to operate, you need a good Opposition.”

title: Gisele Pelicot releases memoir about her abuse
description: Gisele Pelicot has published a memoir after she survived being raped by her ex-husband and dozens of other men he recruited over nearly a decade.  She says she wants her book titled ‘A Hymn to Life: Shame Has to Change Sides’ to be a symbol of hope.  It covers her childhood, marriage, career, as well as the trial of her former husband and the men he recruited.

title: Carnival is underway in Rio De Janeiro
description: Rio De Janeiro’s famous Carnival festival is underway.  Spectators and partygoers crowded the streets for one of the biggest parties in Brazil.  The annual festival attracts millions of visitors.

title: ‘It’s a win’: Flowers remain big hit on Valentine’s Day
description: East Coast Wildflowers Joy Bannister says flowers are all people want to see right now.  Many people are spoiling partners and loved ones today on Valentine’s Day with flowers.  “It’s not a chocolate that I eat and feel bad about,” Ms Bannister said.

title: SWAT operation occurring three kilometres from Nancy Guthrie’s home
description: A SWAT police operation is underway at a property located just over three kilometres from Nancy Guthrie’s home.  There are local reports the warrant has been obtained to search the property.   She is the mother of US TV morning personality Savannah Guthrie.

title: BREAKING: Three detained during SWAT operation in search of Nancy Guthrie
description: Authorities have detained at least three individuals following a SWAT operation near the home of missing Nancy Guthrie.  She is the mother of TV personality Savannah Guthrie, who was born in Melbourne.   Pima County police are expected to provide an update on the investigation soon.   The arrests raise questions about potential ransom demands and the involvement of those apprehended in Guthrie's disappearance.

title: ‘Left-wing media are your enemy’: Rowan Dean blasts Liberal Party machine
description: Sky News host Rowan Dean criticises the Liberal Party’s organisational structure.  “The left-wing media are your enemy, Liberals,” Mr Dean said.  “The Party machine and NSW and across Australia, it’s a joke.  “It should be dismantled. They’re the ones that keep losing.”

title: ‘A tactical threat’: Trump dispatches world’s largest aircraft carrier to Iran
description: University of Otago Professor Robert Patman believes the deployment of the USS Gerald R. Ford signals strategic pressure on Iran rather than imminent conflict.  “The aircraft carrier, the Gerald R. Ford, the largest of its kind in the world, has just been dispatched,” Mr Patman told Sky News Australia.  “It does seem to be that Mr Trump is looking for a deal with this Iranian leadership.  “I think it’s more of a tactical threat.”

title: ‘Someday you’ll find out’: Trump teases classified weapon used in Maduro’s capture
description: US President Donald Trump says foreign-made military equipment failed during Maduro's capture, teasing that “someday” the world will learn why adversaries were unable to respond.  “It was in a matter of minutes before he was on a helicopter being taken out of there,” Mr Trump said.   “That night, the entire world saw what the US military was capable of.  “They even talk about the discombobulator because they never got a shot off.  “The Russian equipment didn’t work, the Chinese equipment didn’t work, everyone’s trying to figure out why it didn’t work.  “Someday you’re going to find out why it didn’t work.”

title: ‘Operation Midnight Hammer’: Trump praises ‘total obliteration’ of Iran’s nuclear capability
description: US President Donald Trump claims Operation Midnight Hammer eliminated Iran’s nuclear potential.  “Last summer I ordered devastating strikes on Iran’s key nuclear facilities, in something that was called Operation Midnight Hammer,” Mr Trump said.   “That was Operation Midnight Hammer achieving total obliteration of Iran's nuclear potential capabilities.  “No other country on earth could have done what we did.”

title: Penman blasts ‘appalling’ housing system for ‘taking from battlers’ and rewarding the ultra-rich
description: Jim’s mowing CEO Jim Penman calls for zoning laws to be lifted to make housing more affordable.  “Our housing is double the cost it should be,” Mr Penman told Sky News host Steve Price  “We need to lift the zoning.   “It’s an appalling situation.  “We are taking money from ordinary people, from battlers and giving it to the ultra-rich property owners.”

title: ‘The heart of the enemy’: Jim’s Mowing CEO vows to ‘attack’ deep green electorate
description: Jim’s Mowing CEO Jim Penman has announced he will run for parliament in what he describes as a “deep green” electorate.  “It’s a deep green seat, it’s going into the heart of the enemy,” Mr Penman told Sky News host Steve Price.  “I want to attack them.”

title: ‘Lies are what they are’: Bishop urges Coalition to expose the government
description: Former speaker of the house Bronwyn Bishop argues the Coalition now has an opportunity to directly call out what she describes as the government’s “lies.”  “He [Angus Taylor] performed well in that first press conference,” Ms Bishop told Sky News host Rowan Dean.  “I think that there’s a team there that has the opportunity to point out the lies of the current government.  “And lies are what they are.”

title: One Nation a ‘formidable force’: Danby warns of growing political threat to Liberals
description: Former Labor MP Michael Danby believes Angus Taylor faces a significant challenge from One Nation.  “He’s [Angus Taylor] got a problem that One Nation is not at 27 per cent,” Mr Danby told Sky News host Rowan Dean.  “They’re [One Nation] going to be a formidable force.”

title: Pressure mounts for Coalition to strike preference deal with One Nation
description: Former speaker of the house Bronwyn Bishop argues the Coalition must consider an accommodation with One Nation to maximise its political position.  “With leadership goes intent and the desire to shape where those preferences goes,” Ms Bishop told Sky News host Rowan Dean.  “There has to be an accommodation with One Nation.  “It does come down to how you manage those preferences.”
